<TITLE> 3 shipbreakers killed in Ctg </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Oct 8 (bdnews24.com)Three workers of a ship-breaking yard were killed after a large iron plate fell on them at Sitakunda's Sheetalpur area in Chittagong on Thursday. 28-year old Mohammad Nasir, 24-year old 'Nahid' and 25-year old Hazrat Ali were workers of Crystal Shipyard. Sitakunda Police Station sub-inspector Abdul Bayes told bdnews24.com the three died on the spot while cutting a scrap ship at around 9:30am. The police are investigating the matter, he said. The bodies wee sent to Chittagong Medical College Hospital for autopsy, Bayes said. A case in underway, he added
